<subSubSection pageId="115" pageNumber="511" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="115.[112,1319,1198,2098]" pageId="115" pageNumber="511">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[115,463,1871,1900]" pageId="115" pageNumber="511">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Near Threatened on The IUCN Red List. Macmillan’s White-toothed Shrew was only known from the holotype until 2001 when three more specimens were obtained. The species has a restricted distribution and may be primarily threatened by deforestation of its montane forest habitat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
